<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910206-0089</DOCNO><DOCID>910206-0089.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Rodman andamp; Renshaw   Picks Norman Mains   To Be Its President</HL><DATE>02/06/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   RR WNEWS</CO><IN>SECURITIES (SCR)</IN><LP>   CHICAGO -- Rodman andamp; Renshaw Capital Group Inc. namedNorman E. Mains, executive vice president of Bateman Eichler,Hill Richards of Los Angeles, as its president and chiefoperating officer.   He succeeds Howard B. Silverman, who resigned last monthafter disagreeing with Kurt B. Karmin, the company's chairmanand chief executive, about the strategy of the financialservices concern.</LP><TEXT>   Before joining Bateman Eichler, Mr. Mains, 47 years old,was director of research at Drexel Burnham Lambert'sinstitutional financial futures and options division inChicago. Mr. Karmin is also an alumnus of the defunct DrexelBurnham brokerage concern, having been senior vice presidentand regional manager in Chicago.   Mr. Mains also had been a senior economist at the FederalReserve Board for seven years.</TEXT></DOC>